{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"T4FN6sDHfA9wxiZ7Dg5WX","title":"Dynamic Factor Models","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"type":"note","desc":"","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"DFM","id":"T4FN6sDHfA9wxiZ7Dg5WX","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"user.forniGeneralizedDynamicFactorModel2000","alias":"@forniGeneralizedDynamicFactorModel2000","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":142,"offset":159},"end":{"line":4,"column":181,"offset":198},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"to":{"fname":"user.forniGeneralizedDynamicFactorModel2000"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"DFM","id":"T4FN6sDHfA9wxiZ7Dg5WX","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"SFM","alias":"SFM","position":{"start":{"line":20,"column":43,"offset":743},"end":{"line":20,"column":50,"offset":750},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"SFM"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"DFM","id":"T4FN6sDHfA9wxiZ7Dg5WX","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"user.forniGeneralizedDynamicFactorModel2000","alias":"@forniGeneralizedDynamicFactorModel2000","position":{"start":{"line":28,"column":16,"offset":1944},"end":{"line":28,"column":55,"offset":1983},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"to":{"fname":"user.forniGeneralizedDynamicFactorModel2000"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"DFM","id":"T4FN6sDHfA9wxiZ7Dg5WX","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"user.forni","alias":"@forni","position":{"start":{"line":28,"column":62,"offset":1990},"end":{"line":28,"column":68,"offset":1996},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"to":{"fname":"user.forni"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"DFM","id":"T4FN6sDHfA9wxiZ7Dg5WX","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"user.forni_generalized_2000","alias":"@forni_generalized_2000","position":{"start":{"line":65,"column":2,"offset":3927},"end":{"line":65,"column":25,"offset":3950},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"to":{"fname":"user.forni_generalized_2000"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"DFM","id":"T4FN6sDHfA9wxiZ7Dg5WX","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"user.forni_generalized_2005","alias":"@forni_generalized_2005","position":{"start":{"line":69,"column":2,"offset":3973},"end":{"line":69,"column":25,"offset":3996},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"to":{"fname":"user.forni_generalized_2005"}}],"anchors":{"nomenclature":{"type":"header","text":"Nomenclature","value":"nomenclature","line":12,"column":0},"dynamic-pca":{"type":"header","text":"Dynamic PCA","value":"dynamic-pca","line":50,"column":0},"dynamic-pca-with-periodic-correlation":{"type":"header","text":"Dynamic PCA with Periodic Correlation","value":"dynamic-pca-with-periodic-correlation","line":61,"column":0},"generalized-dynamic-pca":{"type":"header","text":"Generalized Dynamic PCA","value":"generalized-dynamic-pca","line":66,"column":0},"two-sided-gdfm":{"type":"header","text":"Two sided GDFM","value":"two-sided-gdfm","line":73,"column":0},"one-sided-gdfm":{"type":"header","text":"One sided GDFM","value":"one-sided-gdfm","line":77,"column":0},"unrestricted-gdfm":{"type":"header","text":"Unrestricted GDFM","value":"unrestricted-gdfm","line":80,"column":0}},"fname":"DFM","updated":1638162715776,"created":1634214992986,"parent":"PhD","children":["ghJgufNZMqDjTfu1EKtc1","1jV50YftmiErRFb7OgrEo"],"data":{},"contentHash":"9ce103243e368a3e4ef572c899694bb2","custom":{"geometry":"margin=2cm","bibliography":["references.bib"],"reference-section-title":"References"}},"body":"<h1 id=\"dynamic-factor-models\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#dynamic-factor-models\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Dynamic Factor Models</h1>\n<h2 id=\"nomenclature\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#nomenclature\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Nomenclature</h2>\n<p>This thesis will refer to these as <em>dynamic</em> factor models, as opposed to <em>static</em> factor models. Confusingly, they are also referred to by [<a title=\"Private\" style=\"color: brown\" href=\"https://wiki.dendron.so/notes/hfyvYGJZQiUwQaaxQO27q.html\" target=\"_blank\">@forniGeneralizedDynamicFactorModel2000 (Private)</a>] as <em>Generalized</em> Dynamic Factor Models. </p>\n<p>Stock and Watson denote t a truly dynamic factor model as follows:</p>\n<div class=\"math math-display\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>X</mi><mrow><mi>i</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>λ</mi><mi>i</mi></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>L</mi><msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo mathvariant=\"normal\" lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup><msub><mi>f</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>e</mi><mrow><mi>i</mi><mi>t</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X_{it} = \\lambda_i (L)'f_t + e_{it}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.83333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.31166399999999994em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.07847em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">t</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.051892em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">λ</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.31166399999999994em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">L</span><span class=\"mclose\"><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.801892em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.113em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2805559999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.10764em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">t</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.58056em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">e</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.31166399999999994em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">t</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div>\n<p>where <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>f</mi><mi>t</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f_t</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8888799999999999em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2805559999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.10764em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">t</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is a <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>q</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">q</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">q</span></span></span></span></span> dimensional vector of dynamic factors, also known as primitive shocks, and <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>λ</mi><mi>i</mi></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>L</mi><msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo mathvariant=\"normal\" lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\lambda_i(L)'</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.001892em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">λ</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.31166399999999994em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">L</span><span class=\"mclose\"><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.751892em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> denotes the <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>q</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">q</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">q</span></span></span></span></span> dimensional lag polynomial, also called the \"dynamic factor loadings\".</p>\n<p>Recall that the principal components estimate is formulated to estimate the <em>static</em> factors, which are written as </p>\n<div class=\"math math-display\"><span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Λ</mi><msub><mi>F</mi><mi>t</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><msub><mi>e</mi><mi>t</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X_t = \\Lambda F_t + e_t</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.83333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2805559999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.07847em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">t</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.83333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">Λ</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2805559999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.13889em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">t</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.58056em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">e</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2805559999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">t</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></div>\n<p>For more details on the PC estimator, see <a href=\"/notes/0R61RLuT7e3hswR2v6o0w\">Static Factor Models</a> and its related sections.</p>\n<p>Estimating the dynamic factors directly has proven to be difficult, and is done mainly via dynamic principal components. Static principal components finds the closest approximation of the covariance matrix of <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>t</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X_t</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.83333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2805559999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.07847em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">t</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>, among all covariance matrices of reduced rank. In contrast, dynamic principal components finds the closest approximation to the <em>spectrum</em> of <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>t</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X_t</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.83333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2805559999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.07847em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">t</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>, among all possible spectral density matrices of reduced rank.</p>\n<p>Originally, Brillinger (1981)'s estimation algorithm generalizes static PCA to the frequency domain. The spectral dentisy of <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>t</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X_t</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.83333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2805559999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.07847em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">t</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> is first estimated via some consistent spectral density estimator <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mover accent=\"true\"><mi>S</mi><mo stretchy=\"true\">^</mo></mover><mrow><mi>X</mi><mi>X</mi></mrow></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>ω</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\widehat{S}_{XX}(\\omega)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.17333em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord accent\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.92333em;\"><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05764em;\">S</span></span></span><span class=\"svg-align\" style=\"width:calc(100% - 0.16668em);margin-left:0.16668em;top:-3.6833299999999998em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span style=\"height:0.24em;\"><svg width=\"100%\" height=\"0.24em\" viewBox=\"0 0 1062 239\" preserveAspectRatio=\"none\"><path d=\"M529 0h5l519 115c5 1 9 5 9 10 0 1-1 2-1 3l-4 22\nc-1 5-5 9-11 9h-2L532 67 19 159h-2c-5 0-9-4-11-9l-5-22c-1-6 2-12 8-13z\"></path></svg></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.32833099999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">ω</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span>, at a given frequency <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>ω</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\omega</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.43056em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">ω</span></span></span></span></span>. Next, the eigenvectors corresponding to the <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>q</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">q</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">q</span></span></span></span></span> largest eigenvalues of this matrix are computed. Then, an inverse Fourier Trasform of these eigenvectors yields estimators of the principal component time series using the formulas given. </p>\n<p>Note that because this was originally developed for classical factor analysis, the asymptotics of this under a large <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>N</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">N</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">N</span></span></span></span></span> dimension were not developed by the original author, though as expected asymptotic normality results hold.</p>\n<p>Subsequently, [<a title=\"Private\" style=\"color: brown\" href=\"https://wiki.dendron.so/notes/hfyvYGJZQiUwQaaxQO27q.html\" target=\"_blank\">@forniGeneralizedDynamicFactorModel2000 (Private)</a>] and [<a title=\"Private\" style=\"color: brown\" href=\"https://wiki.dendron.so/notes/hfyvYGJZQiUwQaaxQO27q.html\" target=\"_blank\">@forni (Private)</a> 2004] study the properties of this algorithm, and establish inferential results for the resulting common component estimator. Dyanmic PCA is shown to provide piecewise consistent estimation of the component as <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>N</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">N</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">N</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">T</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span></span></span></span></span> increase, and in their followup, this consistency holds if <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>N</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>T</mi><mo>→</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∞</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">N, T \\rightarrow \\infty</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8777699999999999em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">N</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.43056em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∞</span></span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>N</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi>T</mi><mo>→</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">N/T \\rightarrow 0</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">N</span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.64444em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">0</span></span></span></span></span>, suggesting that some caution to be exercised in finite samples if <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>N</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">N</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10903em;\">N</span></span></span></span></span> is large relative to <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">T</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">T</span></span></span></span></span>.</p>\n<p>Side note: Ben is not sure how often people actually estimate factor models via this method. Trudging through the literature, it seems that this strand was very exciting for a while, but either no one understood it well enough, or it had other significant limitations that no one actually uses it in applied research. In either case, it does not seem like a viable future path.</p>\n<p>Note that because DPCA does not yield a consistent estimator of the common component.</p>\n<p>The generalized factors are preferably to the static factors in the following ways:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>The generalized factors can be directly interpreted as primitive macroeconomic shocks</li>\n<li>The generalized factors' dynamics can often be of interest to applied macreconomists</li>\n<li></li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"dynamic-pca\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#dynamic-pca\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Dynamic PCA</h2>\n<p>Note that this is VERY intensive!\nAlso, outputs don't make too much sense... Need to spend more time studying this</p>\n<p>Beware of other misnomers in the literature! Someone else somewhere referred to dynamic PCA as simply PCA but run on lagged regressors - this is very different to what the rest of the literature at large says!</p>\n<p>freqdom package</p>\n<p>Will need to investigate how Barigozzi's factorcpt (which has been archived on CRAN for not passing checks) works.</p>\n<h2 id=\"dynamic-pca-with-periodic-correlation\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#dynamic-pca-with-periodic-correlation\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Dynamic PCA with Periodic Correlation</h2>\n<p>pcdpca package\nNeed to spend time to play around with this.</p>\n<h2 id=\"generalized-dynamic-pca\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#generalized-dynamic-pca\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Generalized Dynamic PCA</h2>\n<p>gdpc package (fucking mess)</p>\n<p>Methods etc are all broken and even the example code given does not work - no idea how this was approved on CRAN</p>\n<h2 id=\"two-sided-gdfm\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#two-sided-gdfm\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Two sided GDFM</h2>\n<p>[<a title=\"Private\" style=\"color: brown\" href=\"https://wiki.dendron.so/notes/hfyvYGJZQiUwQaaxQO27q.html\" target=\"_blank\">@forni_generalized_2000 (Private)</a>]</p>\n<h2 id=\"one-sided-gdfm\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#one-sided-gdfm\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>One sided GDFM</h2>\n<p>[<a title=\"Private\" style=\"color: brown\" href=\"https://wiki.dendron.so/notes/hfyvYGJZQiUwQaaxQO27q.html\" target=\"_blank\">@forni_generalized_2005 (Private)</a>]</p>\n<h2 id=\"unrestricted-gdfm\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#unrestricted-gdfm\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Unrestricted GDFM</h2>\n<hr>\n<h2 id=\"children\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#children\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Children</h2>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/ghJgufNZMqDjTfu1EKtc1\">Breaks in Dynamic Factor Models</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/1jV50YftmiErRFb7OgrEo\">DFM Inference</a></li>\n</ol>","noteIndex":{"id":"PhD","title":"PhD Homepage","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"type":"note","desc":"","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"PhD","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"user.han_tests_2015","alias":"@han_tests_2015","position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":120,"offset":727},"end":{"line":21,"column":135,"offset":742},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"to":{"fname":"user.han_tests_2015"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"PhD","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"user.baltagi_estimating_2021","alias":"@baltagi_estimating_2021","position":{"start":{"line":21,"column":156,"offset":763},"end":{"line":21,"column":180,"offset":787},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"to":{"fname":"user.baltagi_estimating_2021"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"PhD","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"roadmap","alias":"roadmap","position":{"start":{"line":50,"column":1,"offset":2366},"end":{"line":50,"column":12,"offset":2377},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"roadmap"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"PhD","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"Meeting","alias":"Meeting","position":{"start":{"line":52,"column":1,"offset":2379},"end":{"line":52,"column":12,"offset":2390},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"Meeting"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"PhD","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"TODO","alias":"TODO","position":{"start":{"line":54,"column":1,"offset":2392},"end":{"line":54,"column":9,"offset":2400},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"TODO"}},{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"PhD","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"Misc","alias":"Misc","position":{"start":{"line":56,"column":1,"offset":2402},"end":{"line":56,"column":9,"offset":2410},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"Misc"}}],"anchors":{"latest-meeting-agenda":{"type":"header","text":"Latest Meeting Agenda","value":"latest-meeting-agenda","line":18,"column":0},"quick-links":{"type":"header","text":"Quick Links","value":"quick-links","line":58,"column":0}},"fname":"root","updated":1637898837104,"created":1595961348801,"parent":null,"children":["nA5LxTgruLEzcUt6tzsJT","t58wEmhAtf1GlHmO","CQTUwoXQNcd0Y7la7IaAn","9s2d4L1UHWFWCdtORYT2Q","AiXOWFsdvi3BPZxcUMjIi","MsmFdXyWfizd5g8GGcObD","MXHvc8bQbNRRVCB0UogRy","T4FN6sDHfA9wxiZ7Dg5WX","jtZSk246bVVDfJy6cdpS1","2qGHFR7CcKOE0Meu7UU6D","qGmGYptDKW2WLwlsu2xJw","GvwoAWaYZxq1czYi3t3k4","cTD6yfaUjMoFn0WeWb2jS","ZIDZSAYP9a9L7jYhVMgcz","sZxtv1Zoy8MeQiUDaymMz","WOnXV41UlGcOQzEoTZzJU","fhf7Gdr3mhOUG1mU5twC6","4GXJm4YpHBWVu5WnZKVm4","AOvKFmg0tBcGmUASXaALX","qDVp6IFHf6FiUdSgxwZMA","P1J9LjuSdOyvsaftSsUci","HgXYpL8CJLCszNUOmbHhP","fHzGITjWkNNkiwsQpdex4","umGHrdI4OaLoU8OOAOdkL","aQw5xJBpqunSJYCfXXAls","0R61RLuT7e3hswR2v6o0w","AuDqSlWn0PlsSo8JdLgrR","ElqQePaEuSSz7pSeO1gNc","BMClpTRP3V8ITqM7R4kh0","1ruiVSk3lFpEOUNqPnYti","FNflnQbSXuMwTtni2C8is","y0rpX1u3Lz3vpUFro9TcW"],"data":{},"contentHash":"454a89de45466a7489de7d57126b99fa","custom":{"stub":false,"bibliography":["references.bib"],"reference-section-title":"References","nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"body":"\nWelcome to my website!\n\nThis website has been built using Dendron, and each topic has been collated into collapsible sections on the left hand side. Below is supposed to be a graph view so that you can visualize and explore how topics are connected to one another, but this has not been implemented yet.\n\nThe search functionality is very powerful. Note that default search tries to exact match actual page names - make sure to prefix with ? to get actual search.\n\n## Latest Meeting Agenda\n\nMain points:\n\n- \n\n\nIdeas for new test statistic:\n\nQuestion:\n\nHow many *static* factors are there subject to breaks?\n\n- This is mostly answered, IC are consistent for an equivalent *static* representation without breaks (proposition in [@han_tests_2015], and a comment in [@baltagi_estimating_2021])\n    - These are not that easy to work with, but this covers almost all cases of breaks\n    - A direct implication of this is that structural breaks will *always increase* the no. of static factors estimated\n- However, representation theorems have not considered any breaks in factors that cannot be explained by a change in loadings, due to the multiplicative structure\n    - change in variance of primitive shocks (heteroskedasticity)\n    - mean shift in factor process\n\nDoes overestimation/underestimation actually affect subsequent forecasting?\n- This is a good opportunity to tie in with\n    - Machine Learning thesis (this was essentially forecasting), demonstrating one way which ML methods can break down\n    - CWF project, which ideally could offer a possible solution to this (or at least provide a method that is more robust to breaks)\n\n- Test for structural change one time, vs smooth changes (non parametrics), kink vs curve\n- Test for change in variance of primitive shock innovations (this does not seem to be covered yet)\n- Test for changes in factor dynamics, based on the assumption that the number of primitive factors does not change (seems reasonable enough in economics...?)\n\nHousekeeping\n\n- macroXTS class is finished\n- static $r$ IC have been implemented\n- standard PCA estimator should be fully implemented\n- dynamic $q$ IC are all WIP\n- other estimators of DFMs are not yet implemented\n    - EM estimator (viewed as QMLE)\n    - Bayesian (can of worms)\n    - Spectral density estimator (useful for getting the actual primitive shocks)\n\n## Quick Links\n\n[[roadmap]]\n\n[[Meeting]]\n\n[[TODO]]\n\n[[Misc]]"},"collectionChildren":null,"customHeadContent":null,"config":{"version":4,"useFMTitle":true,"useNoteTitleForLink":true,"mermaid":true,"useKatex":true,"dev":{"enablePreviewV2":true},"site":{"siteUrl":{},"copyAssets":true,"siteHierarchies":["root"],"siteRootDir":"docs","usePrettyRefs":true,"title":"Ze Yu","description":"Personal knowledge space","siteLastModified":true,"gh_edit_branch":"main","duplicateNoteBehavior":{"action":"useVault","payload":["vault","dendron.templates"]},"usePrettyLinks":true,"siteNotesDir":"notes","siteFaviconPath":"favicon.ico","gh_edit_link":true,"gh_edit_link_text":"Edit this page on GitHub","gh_root":"docs/","gh_edit_view_mode":"edit","writeStubs":true,"siteIndex":"root"},"commands":{"lookup":{"note":{"selectionMode":"extract","confirmVaultOnCreate":false,"leaveTrace":false,"bubbleUpCreateNew":true}},"randomNote":{},"insertNote":{"initialValue":"templates"},"insertNoteLink":{"aliasMode":"none","enableMultiSelect":false},"insertNoteIndex":{"enableMarker":false}},"workspace":{"vaults":[{"fsPath":"templates","seed":"dendron.templates","name":"dendron.templates"},{"fsPath":"vault"}],"journal":{"dailyDomain":"daily","name":"journal","dateFormat":"y.MM.dd","addBehavior":"childOfDomain"},"scratch":{"name":"scratch","dateFormat":"y.MM.dd.HHmmss","addBehavior":"asOwnDomain"},"task":{"name":"","dateFormat":"","addBehavior":"childOfCurrent","statusSymbols":{"":" ","wip":"w","done":"x","assigned":"a","moved":"m","blocked"